# Domain-Driven Design — Kafka Tool

## Before any change

1. Read **`docs/DOMAIN.md`** — canonical ubiquitous language and bounded contexts.
2. Use terms from that document in new types, methods, tests, and user-visible strings.
3. If the change adds or alters domain vocabulary, update **`docs/DOMAIN.md`** in the same change (set **Last updated**).

## Naming — no helpers or job titles

- **Forbidden for new types:** simple names ending in `Helper`, `Util`, or `Utils`.
- Prefer **domain nouns** from `docs/DOMAIN.md`: broker profile, topic, record, partition lag, formatted record key, …
- Avoid **job-title suffixes** (`-er`, `-or`): `Formatter`, `Validator`, `Parser`, `Handler`, `Manager`. Put behaviour on the domain object it belongs to.
- The `controls/helpers/` package is legacy UI chrome — do not add new `*Helper` classes there; use domain or UI nouns (`ApplicationWindow`, `WindowResize`, …).

```java
// ❌ BAD — job title, static procedure
public final class KeyFormatter {
    public static String format(byte[] key, KeySerializer s) { … }
}

// ✅ GOOD — domain object encapsulates its value
public final class RecordKey {
    private final byte[] bytes;
    private final KeySerializer serializer;
    public String displayText() { … }
}
```

## Objects, not utility bags

Align with [Seven Virtues of a Good Object](https://www.yegor256.com/2014/11/20/seven-virtues-of-good-object.html):

| Virtue | In this project |
|--------|-----------------|
| Represents real domain | Types map to broker profiles, topics, records, consumer groups — not “parsers” or “validators” in isolation |
| Works by contract | Extract interfaces when mocking or decorating (`inspect/`, `consumers/`, `settings/`) |
| Unique / encapsulates | Each instance wraps specific data (broker name, key bytes, partition id) |
| Immutable | Prefer `record` and `final`; no setters on value objects (see `.cursor/rules/immutability.mdc`) |
| No static domain API | Avoid new `public static` methods on domain types; use instance methods or small factories |
| Name = what it is | `RecordValue`, not `RecordValueFormatter` |
| `final` or `abstract` | New concrete domain classes are `final` unless extension is intentional |

## Layer placement

| Kind | Package |
|------|---------|
| Broker profiles, persistence, validation | `settings/` |
| Admin inspection, DTOs, cluster snapshots | `inspect/` |
| Consume, fetch, key/value display logic | `consumers/` |
| UI table rows, screen state | `viewmodels/`, controllers orchestrate only |

Tell, don't ask: see `.cursor/rules/java-quality.mdc`. Controllers must not re-implement rules already owned by domain types.

## Checklist before finishing

- [ ] Names match **`docs/DOMAIN.md`**
- [ ] No new `*Helper` / `*Util` types
- [ ] Domain doc updated if vocabulary or behaviour changed
- [ ] Gherkin scenario descriptions use the same language (`.cursor/rules/tdd-gherkin.mdc`)
